<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Aean on 04-08-2002 02:10 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">No, do not do the testament of vanear, the thing has no ac and is no worth it. That thing is much better for druids.
heheh I just looked at your profile, there are very few human clerics out there and even fewer Mith Marr clerics. There are 2 I know of on my server, and i'm one of them. There is a bad ass cleric on these boards by the name of Arturo, he's one as well. welcome to the few and the proud ;)

ok if you have 1k a slot then that is ALOT to play with. I would definately listen to people about the HP/AC rings, they will help you SO much. Maybe some moonstone rings would help out with the mana. I am a real stickler about AC and will more often than not give up wis for AC. Also as a human cleric you can do some awsome quests from Paineel, the helmet is the hardest one to do but you will keep that thing on you permanently just for the effect, and it rules against dispelling mobs.

for the offhand get a charred guardian shield, ac10 wis9, usually goes for 2-300 (all prices will be ones from my server so they might be different for you)
2 6ac/65hp rings  1k for the set
Skull Shaped Barbute  150pp ish
cleric quest bracers  usually 1k each but they will last you a LONG time
donals arms  sell for under 1k now
Blackened Alloy Medallion  400pp
Gauntlets of the black  200pp  (which is a far cry from the 5k i paid when they first came out hahaha)
Cleric quest boots and legs  200pp each
Forest Loops for the ears, 300pp each
Adamantite Epolets  200pp
Straw Spun Belt  25pp

now with all that, and i'm asuming you have the 1k per slot, thats gonna leave you alot of money left over, I'd suggest a Seb Scale Coat and legs, they are about 2k each, but they're gonna last you well into your planes levels. Mammoth Hide Cloak still sells for around 1k and is very good

Your weapon is decent, but you will find you wont' be meleeing a whole lot so it's not really worth upgrading. it's fast which is nice so you can work on your 1HB skill pretty quickly.

With a list of items like that you'll have very good AC and decent wis. you can switch out the ac/hp rings for moonstone rings if you're running outa mana too often. When you get higher in level, once you can Imbue Diamonds which is level 29, you can find a chanter and get some Imbued Mith Marr rings made  5wis 5 to all saves which are amazing rings. and if you're going to start doing those paineel quests DO NOT atempt them untill you are in your 30s at least, or have lots of friends to help. I tried the helmet quest when i was 20, and i managed to get all the items i needed, but i could have spent all that time leveling instead and making it easier when i was a more appropriate level</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
